# Phase One: Institutionalizing OER

Elements of Phase One include:

* Reach out to student government to collaborate in the support of OER and open textbooks specifically 
* Draft a student government senate resolution supporting the institutionalization of OER, including the promotion of, support for, and incentivization for faculty to use open textbooks.
* Create and host student workshops on OER 
* Recruit students to Phase Two student-led open projects 
 
 # Examples of student resolutions in support of OER 
 
Resolutions

* [Resolution: Textbook	Affordability	and	Open Education	Resources](https://www.valleycollege.edu/about-sbvc/campus-committees/academic-senate/documents/resolution_sp16.01.pdf) ([San Bernardino Valley College faculty and students](https://www.valleycollege.edu/open-education-resources/))
* [Resolution: X](http://www.naacp.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/NAACPOERResolutionFinalRatified.pdf) ([NAAP](http://www.naacp.org/campaigns/open-education-resources-equity-opportunities/))

